gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 109, Thunder 105
gameRecap.excerpt: Joel Embiid put up 24 points (6-14 FG), six rebounds and seven assists in his return as the 76ers defeated the Thunder, 109-105. Kelly Oubre Jr. added a game-high 25 points (4-7 3PT FG), along with six rebounds for the 76ers in the victory, while Chet Holmgren tallied 22 points (3-6 3PT FG) and seven rebounds for the Thunder in the losing effort. The 76ers have won back-to-back games as they improve to 41-35 on the season, while the Thunder fall to 52-23.
